cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "AI Eval Engine: Domain-Aware Evaluation for Production AI Agents"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using these metadata."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Shivika
    family-names: Bisen
    email: shivikakbisen@gmail.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/sbisen/ai-eval-engine"
url: "https://github.com/sbisen/ai-eval-engine"
abstract: >-
  AI Eval Engine is an open-source Python framework that automates domain-aware
  evaluation of production AI agents. It ingests a pluggable domain context,
  generates a versioned golden set, emits a runnable evaluation script with
  correctness, confidence, and format scores, and maintains a living Safety
  Runbook of emergent failure modes.
keywords:
  - llm
  - evaluation
  - ai-agents
  - domain-aware
  - golden-set
  - llm-as-judge
  - safety
license: MIT
